{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_7","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc 'gh auth status'","aggregated_output":"github.com\n  ✓ Logged in to github.com account josephgreffenkomala (keyring)\n  - Active account: true\n  - Git operations protocol: https\n  - Token: ghp_************************************\n  - Token scopes: 'admin:org', 'gist', 'repo', 'workflow'\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_6","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc 'gh pr view 64 --repo GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular --json number,title,body,state,isDraft,headRefName,baseRefName,reviewDecision,additions,deletions,changedFiles,reviews,comments'","aggregated_output":"{\"additions\":15633,\"baseRefName\":\"develop\",\"body\":\"## Summary\\nAdd an automated PR review workflow built around an OpenCode agent, repo config, and a polling script for drafting and optionally submitting GitHub reviews.\\n\\n## How to Test\\n1. Review `pr-review.conf` and update values if needed.\\n2. Run the PR review script against a target PR and verify it creates draft output and worktree state as expected.\\n3. Confirm the OpenCode agent config in `opencode.json` and `.opencode/agents/pr-review.md` matches the intended permission model.\\n\\n## Related Issues\\nNone.\\n\\n## Author Checklist\\n- [x] Code follows team coding standards and style guide\\n- [x] Self-reviewed the code changes\\n- [ ] Added/updated tests for new functionality\\n- [ ] All tests pass locally\\n- [x] Code is properly documented\\n- [x] Synced with latest `develop` branch\\n- [x] PR title follows conventional commit format\\n- [x] Meaningful commit messages used\\n\\n## Additional Notes\\n- Commit was created with `--no-verify` because `scripts/pr-review.py` currently fails the repo's Ruff/docstring/type-annotation hooks.\\n- `.opencode/package-lock.json` is intentionally force-added despite the local ignore rule.\\n\\n## Type of task\\n- [ ] Data Processing\\n- [ ] Model Training\\n- [ ] API Development\\n- [ ] UI Development\\n- [ ] Testing\\n- [x] Debugging\\n- [ ] Refactor\\n- [ ] Performance Improvement / Optimization\\n- [ ] Security\\n- [x] Documentation\\n- [ ] Monitoring\\n- [ ] All\\n\",\"changedFiles\":89,\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDORoK3as8AAAABF2TCDw\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"## PR Reviewer Guide 🔍\\n\\nHere are some key observations to aid the review process:\\n\\n<table>\\n<tr><td>⏱️&nbsp;<strong>Estimated effort to review</strong>: 4 🔵🔵🔵🔵⚪</td></tr>\\n<tr><td>🧪&nbsp;<strong>No relevant tests</strong></td></tr>\\n<tr><td>🔒&nbsp;<strong>Security concerns</strong><br><br>\\n\\n<strong>Command injection:</strong><br> `notify_command` from `pr-review.conf` is executed via `subprocess.run(..., shell=True)`. If that config value is ever influenced by untrusted input or copied from an unsafe source, it allows arbitrary shell command execution on the review host. Consider avoiding `shell=True` and parsing the command into explicit arguments, or strictly validating/whitelisting allowed notify commands.</td></tr>\\n<tr><td>⚡&nbsp;<strong>Recommended focus areas for review</strong><br><br>\\n\\n<details><summary><a href='https://github.com/GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular/pull/64/files#diff-538e213f212d6ff2de93a4ba544b3d06aacbbfe6bd7546463d3d407deb119a64R140-R147'><strong>Config Ignored</strong></a>\\n\\nThe newly added `skip_draft_prs` and `skip_bot_authors` settings are not read or enforced anywhere in the script, so the tool may review draft PRs and bot-authored PRs despite the configuration indicating otherwise.\\n</summary>\\n\\n```python\\nconf.repo = data.get(\\\"repository\\\", \\\"\\\")\\nconf.model = data.get(\\\"model\\\", \\\"\\\")\\nconf.agent = data.get(\\\"agent\\\", \\\"pr-review\\\")\\nconf.interval = data.get(\\\"interval_seconds\\\", 600)\\nconf.timeout = data.get(\\\"timeout_seconds\\\", 300)\\nconf.notify = data.get(\\\"notify_command\\\", \\\"\\\")\\nconf.editor = data.get(\\\"editor\\\", \\\"\\\")\\n\\n\\n```\\n\\n</details>\\n\\n<details><summary><a href='https://github.com/GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular/pull/64/files#diff-538e213f212d6ff2de93a4ba544b3d06aacbbfe6bd7546463d3d407deb119a64R857-R904'><strong>Review Duplication</strong></a>\\n\\nInline comments are submitted separately from the main review, which can create multiple independent review artifacts and lose the intended association between findings and the review body. Validate that this matches the desired GitHub review behavior.\\n</summary>\\n\\n```python\\nif review_body:\\n    body_file = DATA_DIR / f\\\"pr-{pr_num}-review-body.md\\\"\\n    body_file.write_text(review_body)\\n    result = subprocess.run(\\n        [\\\"gh\\\", \\\"pr\\\", \\\"review\\\", str(pr_num), \\\"--repo\\\", conf.repo, \\\"--comment\\\", \\\"--body-file\\\", str(body_file)],\\n        capture_output=True,\\n        text=True,\\n        check=False,\\n    )\\n    if result.returncode != 0:\\n        err(f\\\"Failed to submit review: {result.stderr[:200]}\\\")\\n        set_pr_state(pr_num, \\\"status\\\", \\\"failed\\\")\\n        set_pr_state(pr_num, \\\"error_message\\\", f\\\"gh pr review failed: {result.stderr[:200]}\\\")\\n        return False\\n    review_submitted = True\\n    ok(f\\\"Review submitted for PR #{pr_num}!\\\")\\n\\nif valid_comments and head_sha:\\n    import json as _json\\n\\n    log(f\\\"  Posting {len(valid_comments)} inline comment(s)...\\\")\\n    posted = 0\\n    for c in valid_comments:\\n        payload = _json.dumps(\\n            {\\n                \\\"body\\\": c[\\\"body\\\"],\\n                \\\"commit_id\\\": head_sha,\\n                \\\"path\\\": c[\\\"path\\\"],\\n                \\\"line\\\": int(c[\\\"line\\\"]),\\n                \\\"side\\\": \\\"RIGHT\\\",\\n            }\\n        )\\n        args = [\\n            \\\"gh\\\",\\n            \\\"api\\\",\\n            \\\"-X\\\",\\n            \\\"POST\\\",\\n            f\\\"repos/{conf.repo}/pulls/{pr_num}/comments\\\",\\n            \\\"--input\\\",\\n            \\\"-\\\",\\n        ]\\n        result = subprocess.run(args, input=payload, capture_output=True, text=True, check=False)\\n        if result.returncode != 0:\\n            warn(f\\\"  Failed to post comment on {c['path']}:{c['line']}: {result.stderr[:120]}\\\")\\n        else:\\n            posted += 1\\n    if posted:\\n        log(f\\\"  Posted {posted}/{len(valid_comments)} inline comment(s)\\\")\\n\\n```\\n\\n</details>\\n\\n<details><summary><a href='https://github.com/GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular/pull/64/files#diff-538e213f212d6ff2de93a4ba544b3d06aacbbfe6bd7546463d3d407deb119a64R777-R779'><strong>Index Error</strong></a>\\n\\nThe terminal feedback flow can raise an exception when the first entered line is blank, because it accesses a previous list element before confirming enough lines exist.\\n</summary>\\n\\n```python\\nif line == \\\"\\\" and lines and lines[-2] == \\\"\\\":\\n    lines.pop()\\n    break\\n\\n```\\n\\n</details>\\n\\n</td></tr>\\n</table>\\n\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-12T04:22:49Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular/pull/64#issuecomment-4687446543\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":false},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDORoK3as8AAAABF2TF3Q\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"## PR Code Suggestions ✨\\n\\n<!-- 56438a8 -->\\n\\nExplore these optional code suggestions:\\n\\n<table><thead><tr><td><strong>Category</strong></td><td align=left><strong>Suggestion&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </strong></td><td align=center><strong>Impact</strong></td></tr><tbody><tr><td rowspan=2>Possible issue</td>\\n<td>\\n\\n\\n\\n<details><summary>Prevent blank-line input crash</summary>\\n\\n___\\n\\n\\n**The double-Enter termination check can raise <code>IndexError</code> on the first blank line <br>because it unconditionally reads <code>lines[-2]</code> after only appending one element. Guard <br>this with a length check so revision input does not crash the interactive flow.**\\n\\n[scripts/pr-review.py [763-780]](https://github.com/GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular/pull/64/files#diff-538e213f212d6ff2de93a4ba544b3d06aacbbfe6bd7546463d3d407deb119a64R763-R780)\\n\\n```diff\\n def input_feedback(pr_num):\\n     print()\\n     print(f\\\"{YELLOW}Enter your feedback for PR #{pr_num}.{NC}\\\")\\n     print(f\\\"{YELLOW}Press Enter twice or type 'done' to finish.{NC}\\\")\\n     print()\\n     lines = []\\n     while True:\\n         try:\\n             line = input()\\n         except (EOFError, KeyboardInterrupt):\\n             break\\n         if line.strip().lower() == \\\"done\\\":\\n             break\\n         lines.append(line)\\n-        if line == \\\"\\\" and lines and lines[-2] == \\\"\\\":\\n+        if line == \\\"\\\" and len(lines) >= 2 and lines[-2] == \\\"\\\":\\n             lines.pop()\\n             break\\n     return \\\"\\\\n\\\".join(lines)\\n```\\n<details><summary>Suggestion importance[1-10]: 8</summary>\\n\\n__\\n\\nWhy: This is a correct bug fix: in `input_feedback()`, entering a blank line first makes `lines[-2]` invalid after only one append, causing an `IndexError`. The proposed `len(lines) >= 2` guard directly fixes an interactive crash in a user-facing flow.\\n\\n\\n</details></details></td><td align=center>Medium\\n\\n</td></tr><tr><td>\\n\\n\\n\\n<details><summary>Request the missing branch field</summary>\\n\\n___\\n\\n\\n**The PR state creation later reads <code>headRefName</code>, but this field is never requested <br>from GitHub here. As a result, <code>branch</code> is always persisted as empty, which can break <br>follow-up logic that depends on the branch name or make state/debugging misleading.**\\n\\n[scripts/pr-review.py [248-262]](https://github.com/GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular/pull/64/files#diff-538e213f212d6ff2de93a4ba544b3d06aacbbfe6bd7546463d3d407deb119a64R248-R262)\\n\\n```diff\\n result = run_cmd(\\n     [\\n         \\\"gh\\\",\\n         \\\"pr\\\",\\n         \\\"list\\\",\\n         \\\"--repo\\\",\\n         conf.repo,\\n         \\\"--state\\\",\\n         \\\"open\\\",\\n         \\\"--json\\\",\\n-        \\\"number,title,headRefOid,baseRefOid,author,isDraft\\\",\\n+        \\\"number,title,headRefOid,baseRefOid,headRefName,author,isDraft\\\",\\n         \\\"--limit\\\",\\n         \\\"100\\\",\\n     ]\\n )\\n```\\n<details><summary>Suggestion importance[1-10]: 6</summary>\\n\\n__\\n\\nWhy: The suggestion is accurate: `create_pending_state()` reads `pr_data.get(\\\"headRefName\\\", \\\"\\\")`, but `fetch_open_prs()` does not request `headRefName`, so `branch` is always empty. This is a real correctness/maintainability issue, though the current PR does not show any immediate functional use of `branch`.\\n\\n\\n</details></details></td><td align=center>Low\\n\\n</td></tr><tr><td rowspan=1>Security</td>\\n<td>\\n\\n\\n\\n<details><summary>Remove shell-based command execution</summary>\\n\\n___\\n\\n\\n**Executing <code>notify_command</code> with <code>shell=True</code> allows arbitrary shell injection if the <br>configured command or substituted draft path contains shell metacharacters. Invoke <br>the command without a shell and split it safely before execution.**\\n\\n[scripts/pr-review.py [675-680]](https://github.com/GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular/pull/64/files#diff-538e213f212d6ff2de93a4ba544b3d06aacbbfe6bd7546463d3d407deb119a64R675-R680)\\n\\n```diff\\n if conf.notify:\\n     cmd = conf.notify.replace(\\\"{PR_NUMBER}\\\", str(pr_num)).replace(\\\"{DRAFT_FILE}\\\", draft_file)\\n     try:\\n-        subprocess.run(cmd, shell=True, capture_output=True, timeout=30, check=False)\\n+        subprocess.run(\\n+            cmd if isinstance(cmd, list) else __import__(\\\"shlex\\\").split(cmd),\\n+            shell=False,\\n+            capture_output=True,\\n+            timeout=30,\\n+            check=False,\\n+        )\\n     except Exception:\\n         pass\\n```\\n<details><summary>Suggestion importance[1-10]: 7</summary>\\n\\n__\\n\\nWhy: The suggestion identifies a legitimate security risk in `notify_user()`: using `subprocess.run(..., shell=True)` with configurable input can enable command injection. The exact replacement is somewhat rough due to dynamic `shlex` importing and changed command semantics, but the core recommendation is still important and relevant.\\n\\n</details></details></td><td align=center>Medium\\n\\n</td></tr></tr></tbody></table>\\n\\n\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-12T04:23:02Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular/pull/64#issuecomment-4687447517\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":false},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDORoK3as8AAAABF3Ko9Q\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"START REVIEW\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:08:07Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular/pull/64#issuecomment-4688357621\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":false},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDORoK3as8AAAABGcI9Xw\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"START REVIEW\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-17T07:18:37Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular/pull/64#issuecomment-4727127391\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":false},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDORoK3as8AAAABG_haTw\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"START REVIEW — submitting automated REQUEST_CHANGES review on PR #64 (head: dfaba6db). Inline comments + summary body follow.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-22T02:37:31Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular/pull/64#issuecomment-4764228175\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":false},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDORoK3as8AAAABG_oAbw\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"## Timeline follow-up: design pattern clue\\n\\nThe auto-review-pr scripts would integrate more cleanly with both **OpenCode** and **Pi** if the provider/backend boundary were formalized with a pattern.\\n\\n**Candidate:** Hexagonal Architecture (Ports & Adapters) for the core review pipeline, plus **Strategy + Factory** for provider backends (OpenCode, Pi, and future agents).\\n\\n**Why it helps:**\\n- **Ports** define a stable core contract (submit review, fetch diff, post comment) independent of any agent harness.\\n- **Adapters** encapsulate each tool\\\\&#39;s CLI/SDK quirks (gh, OpenCode, Pi) behind one interface — swapping or adding a backend becomes a new adapter, not core edits.\\n- **Strategy + Factory** picks the right backend at runtime from config, so callers stay agnostic of which reviewer is active.\\n- Future backends (CI runners, other agents) drop in without touching the review orchestration logic.\\n\\nNet: cleaner seams between review logic and tool integrations, easier testing, and a path to multi-provider support without churn.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-22T03:05:54Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular/pull/64#issuecomment-4764336239\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":false}],\"deletions\":0,\"headRefName\":\"auto-review-pr\",\"isDraft\":true,\"number\":64,\"reviewDecision\":\"CHANGES_REQUESTED\",\"reviews\":[{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoYyQ\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoYyg\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoYzg\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoYzw\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoY0A\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoY0Q\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoY0g\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoY1w\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoY2g\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoY2w\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoY3w\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoY4A\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoY4g\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoY5A\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoY5g\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoY6A\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoY8w\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoZEg\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:07Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoZGQ\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:07Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABCzoe8Q\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"david-gdp\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"This PR introduces automated PR review using OpenCode. The architecture is well-documented. Blocking issues:\\n\\n1. **Script is monolithic and unmaintainable** — 1305 lines in a single flat file with no module separation. Config, state, worktree, review, UI, and submission logic are all tangled together. This needs to be broken into a proper Python package before it grows further.\\n\\n2. **Only 1 PR reviewed per poll cycle** — `process_pending_prs()` hardcodes `break` after the first successful review. If 5 PRs are open, 4 sit idle for 10+ minutes. Remove the PoC-mode limitation.\\n\\n3. **Review submission ignores agent intent** — `approve_pr()` always posts `--comment` regardless of the agent's `Overall Assessment` (APPROVE/REQUEST_CHANGES/COMMENT). The assessment line is never parsed.\\n\\n4. **Inline comments are standalone, not review comments** — Posted via `gh api repos/{repo}/pulls/{num}/comments` which creates standalone PR comments, not review comments associated with the review event. Should use the `repos/{repo}/pulls/{num}/reviews` endpoint.\\n\\n5. **Missing .gitignore** — Runtime files (`state_PR.json`, `.pr-review/`) are documented as \\\"gitignored\\\" in README but no `.gitignore` change was included in this PR. These files contain session IDs and draft reviews that must not be committed.\\n\\n6. **Shell injection risk in notify_user** — Uses `subprocess.run(cmd, shell=True, ...)` with string substitution. Use `shlex.split()` + `shell=False`.\\n\\n7. **No tests** — 1305 lines of automation logic with zero unit or integration test coverage.\\n\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:20Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"CHANGES_REQUESTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"0dfbddd45182b49c9ddb642f0ce16660baaa51f3\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABC-6G6g\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"COLLABORATOR\",\"body\":\"## Re: Blocking Issues — All Resolved\\n\\nThanks for the thorough review. All 7 blocking issues have been addressed in the latest commits on this branch. Here's the summary:\\n\\n---\\n\\n**1. Monolithic 1305-line script** → **Resolved.** Decomposed into `scripts/pr_review/` package with 9 modules: `config.py`, `state.py`, `worktree.py`, `review.py`, `github.py`, `parser.py`, `cli.py`, `commands.py`, `daemon.py`.\\n\\n**2. Only 1 PR reviewed per poll cycle** → **Resolved.** `process_pending_prs()` now uses `ThreadPoolExecutor` with configurable `max_workers` (default 4). No `break` after first review.\\n\\n**3. Review submission ignores agent intent** → **Resolved.** `parser.py` parses `### Overall Assessment` and maps it to `APPROVE`/`REQUEST_CHANGES`/`COMMENT`. `submit_review()` sends `\\\"event\\\": preview.assessment` in the review payload.\\n\\n**4. Inline comments are standalone, not review comments** → **Resolved.** `submit_review()` now posts to `repos/{repo}/pulls/{pr_number}/reviews` with inline comments nested in the `comments` field as a single review event.\\n\\n**5. Missing .gitignore** → **Resolved.** Root `.gitignore` now includes `applications/auto-review-pr/state_PR.json` and `applications/auto-review-pr/.pr-review/`.\\n\\n**6. Shell injection risk in notify_user** → **Resolved.** `notify_user()` now uses `split_user_command()` (backed by `shlex.split()`) and `run_command()` which never uses `shell=True`.\\n\\n**7. No tests** → **Resolved.** 9 unit test modules under `tests/unit/pr_review/` plus `tests/integration/test_pr_review_workflow.py`.\\n\\n---\\n\\nAdditional issues from inline comments also resolved:\\n\\n- **8. IndexError in `input_feedback()`** → Guard: `len(lines) >= DOUBLE_BLANK_LINE_COUNT`.\\n- **9. Missing `headRefName` in `fetch_open_prs()`** → Added to `--json` fields.\\n- **10. `skip_draft_prs`/`skip_bot_authors` not enforced** → `detect_changes()` now checks both with `is_bot_author()` helper.\\n- **11. Signal handler doesn't flush state** → `_shutdown()` calls `_STATE[0].flush()`.\\n- **12. No state caching** → `StateStore` uses in-memory cache with dirty tracking and explicit `flush()`.\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-15T07:15:40Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"4f5c10903f95c0b3e11f397a5f273bd14e960cd4\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABC-7Pnw\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"COLLABORATOR\",\"body\":\"## Re: Inline Review Comments — All Resolved\\n\\nReplies to each inline comment from the original review. All issues have been addressed in the refactored codebase.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Original comment on `scripts/pr-review.py:685` — `approve_pr()` always submits with `--comment`**\\n→ **Resolved.** `submit_review()` in `github.py` now parses the agent's `### Overall Assessment` and sends `\\\"event\\\": preview.assessment` (APPROVE/REQUEST_CHANGES/COMMENT) in the review payload.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Original comment on `scripts/pr-review.py:750` — Skipped comments not surfaced**\\n→ **Resolved.** `_confirm_skipped_comments()` in `cli.py` now prompts the user with count and reasons before submission.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Original comment on `scripts/pr-review.py:200` — Config values not validated**\\n→ **Resolved.** `Config` is now `@dataclass(frozen=True)` with `_require_type()` validation raising `ConfigError` for invalid values.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Original comment on `scripts/pr-review.py:890` — Editor commands with arguments**\\n→ **Resolved.** `split_user_command()` (backed by `shlex.split()`) correctly handles multi-argument editor commands like `code --wait`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Original comment on `scripts/pr-review.py:160` — `cmd.split()` breaks on spaces**\\n→ **Resolved.** `run_command()` now accepts `Sequence[str]` args throughout. No string splitting on commands.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Original comment on `scripts/pr-review.py:750` — Standalone inline comments**\\n→ **Resolved.** `submit_review()` posts to `repos/{repo}/pulls/{pr_number}/reviews` with comments nested in a single review event.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Original comment on `scripts/pr-review.py:718` — Hardcoded 1 PR per cycle**\\n→ **Resolved.** `process_pending_prs()` uses `ThreadPoolExecutor` with `max_workers=4`. No `break` after first review.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Original comment on `scripts/pr-review.py:820` — Fragile regex for inline comments**\\n→ **Resolved.** `parser.py` uses a compiled `INLINE_PATTERN` regex with proper dataclass output.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Original comment on `scripts/pr-review.py:930` — Parser uses `add_help=False`**\\n→ **Resolved.** CLI now uses standard `argparse` with `--model` and `--pr` flags.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Original comment on `scripts/pr-review.py:420` — No timeout on git operations**\\n→ **Resolved.** `run_command()` accepts explicit `timeout` parameter; all git operations pass appropriate timeouts.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Original comment on `scripts/pr-review.py:595` — `shell=True` in notify_user**\\n→ **Resolved.** `notify_user()` uses `split_user_command()`/`shlex.split()` with `run_command()` — no `shell=True`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Original comment on `scripts/pr-review.py:905` — Signal handler doesn't flush**\\n→ **Resolved.** `_shutdown()` calls `_STATE[0].flush()` before `raise SystemExit(0)`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Original comment on `scripts/pr-review.py:1` — Monolithic 1305-line script**\\n→ **Resolved.** Decomposed into `scripts/pr_review/` package with 9 modules.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Original comment on `scripts/pr-review.py:320` — No state caching**\\n→ **Resolved.** `StateStore` uses in-memory cache with dirty tracking and explicit `flush()`.\\n\\n---\\n\\nFor the low/medium-priority items not directly addressed:\\n- `.conf` extension for JSON: acknowledged, low priority.\\n- Hardcoded model/repo in config: these are user config values, not hardcoded defaults. Auto-detection exists via `_detect_repository()`.\\n- `$schema` external URL: opencode convention, not vendorable.\\n- Mixed Indonesian/English README: will standardize in a follow-up.\\n- Duplicate agent permissions: intentional — `opencode.json` is machine-readable, markdown is documentation.\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-15T07:18:09Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"4f5c10903f95c0b3e11f397a5f273bd14e960cd4\"}},{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDORoK3as8AAAABC_ANEQ\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"COLLABORATOR\",\"body\":\"\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:04Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"re