\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/forecast-reviewer/scripts/review_forecast.py:13:  uv run .agents/skills/forecast-reviewer/scripts/review_forecast.py \\\\\ntests/unit/cli/utils/test_forecast_reviewer.py:15:    script_path = root / \"gl_tabular\" / \"templates\" / \"skills\" / \"forecast-reviewer\" / \"scripts\" / \"review_forecast.py\"\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/forecast-reviewer/SKILL.md:2:name: forecast-reviewer\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/forecast-reviewer/SKILL.md:75:4. After modeling reruns and rewrites the prediction artifact, run forecast-reviewer again.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/forecast-reviewer/references/segment-review-patterns.md:3:Patterns for decomposing forecast quality below the aggregate level. Use during the Entity and Segment Decomposition step of `forecast-reviewer`.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/shared/anomaly-detection-contract.md:13:- Forecasting-only gates do not apply: no `forecast-reviewer`, anchor contract, recursive parity, or MAPE progression gate\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/forecast-reviewer/references/forecast-anti-patterns.md:3:Diagnostic reference for recurring failure modes in tabular forecasting runs. Use during the Feature Contribution Audit and Temporal Pattern Fidelity steps of `forecast-reviewer`.\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/__init__.py:13:    STAGE_ORDER,\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/__init__.py:31:    \"STAGE_ORDER\",\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/artifact_schemas.py:47:    FORECAST_REVIEWER = \"forecast-reviewer\"\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/artifact_schemas.py:56:    EXPERIMENT_REVIEW = \"experiment-review\"\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/artifact_schemas.py:58:    FORECAST_REVIEWER = \"forecast-reviewer\"\ngl_tabular/cli/commands/experiment.py:784:    script_path = _PACKAGE_ROOT / \"templates\" / \"skills\" / \"forecast-reviewer\" / \"scripts\" / \"review_forecast.py\"\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/leakage-guard/SKILL.md:53:### Phase 2 — Post (after modeling, before forecast-reviewer / evaluator)\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/leakage-guard/SKILL.md:75:11. If `verdict` is `pass`: record in `current.md` and pass to `forecast-reviewer` (time-series) or `evaluator` (other tasks). For `anomaly_detection`, pass directly to `evaluator`.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/leakage-guard/SKILL.md:203:  \"recommended_next\": \"forecast-reviewer\"\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/artifact_validation.py:19:    route_after_evaluator,\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/artifact_validation.py:20:    route_after_forecast_review,\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/artifact_validation.py:64:        expected_next = route_after_forecast_review(schema.verdict.value)\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/artifact_validation.py:142:            expected_next = route_after_evaluator(schema.verdict.value, task_type, schema.fail_reason)\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/evaluator/references/anomaly-detection-checks.md:47:  \"recommended_next\": \"experiment-review\"\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/references/experiment-decision.md:95:See `../../forecast-reviewer/references/forecast-anti-patterns.md` for the full anti-pattern catalogue with symptoms, detection steps, and remediation hypotheses.\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/stage.py:99:STAGE_ORDER: tuple[str, ...] = (\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/stage.py:107:    \"experiment-review\",\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/stage.py:214:    \"experiment-review\": StageMetadata(\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/stage.py:215:        name=\"experiment-review\",\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/stage.py:221:        skill_path=skill_path_for(\"experiment-review\"),\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/stage.py:273:    for stage in STAGE_ORDER:\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/stage.py:340:    return STAGE_ORDER\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/evaluator/references/forecast-prediction-checks.md:93:See `../../forecast-reviewer/references/forecast-anti-patterns.md` → \"Sentinel Fill Contamination\" for root cause and remediation.\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/routing.py:22:def route_after_forecast_review(verdict: str) -> str:\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/routing.py:23:    \"\"\"Route after forecast-reviewer verdict.\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/routing.py:43:        'forecast-reviewer' for time_series, 'evaluator' otherwise.\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/routing.py:46:        return \"forecast-reviewer\"\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/routing.py:83:def route_after_evaluator(verdict: str, task_type: str, fail_reason: str | None = None) -> str:\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/routing.py:95:        return \"experiment-review\"\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/routing.py:102:        return \"forecast-reviewer\"\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/routing.py:104:    return \"experiment-review\"\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/routing.py:126:    routed = route_after_evaluator(verdict, task_type, fail_reason)\ngl_tabular/cli/utils/experiment/routing.py:127:    if routed != \"experiment-review\":\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/SKILL.md:76:For `anomaly_detection` tasks, the same stage order applies. Use `../shared/anomaly-detection-contract.md` as the shared methodology and routing contract. `data-analysis` owns the methodology decision, `feature-engineer` owns any required data view, `modeling` owns PyOD training and self-checks, and `evaluator` owns independent score/metric verification. `forecast-reviewer`, anchor checks, recursive parity checks, and MAPE progression gates do not apply to anomaly detection.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/SKILL.md:80:Out-of-band routing (leakage-guard, forecast-reviewer) is enforced by `gl_tabular.cli.utils.experiment.routing.resolve_next_stage` (now implemented). The `checkpoint` command reads gate artifacts and routes accordingly — do not override routing in prompt logic.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/SKILL.md:116:`forecast-reviewer` (now implemented as a specialist skill) does not produce a persisted script. It produces `applications/{task}/experiments/artifacts/forecast_review.json`. Do not scaffold a `.py` for this stage. Delegate it by passing the modeling self-check results, prediction artifact path, and task context (not the evaluator verdict — forecast-reviewer runs before evaluator).\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/SKILL.md:149:### Post (after modeling, before forecast-reviewer / evaluator)\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/SKILL.md:151:After `modeling` self-check gate passes and before delegating `forecast-reviewer` (time-series) or `evaluator` (other tasks):\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/SKILL.md:167:4. If verdict is `pass`: proceed to `forecast-reviewer` (time-series) or `evaluator` (other tasks).\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/SKILL.md:169:For `anomaly_detection`, a passing post gate proceeds directly to `evaluator`. Do not run `forecast-reviewer`.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/SKILL.md:173:After `modeling` completes and before delegating `evaluator`, run `forecast-reviewer` for all forecasting and time-aware regression tasks:\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/SKILL.md:175:1. Delegate `forecast-reviewer` with the prediction artifact path, training target stats, inference mode, forecast horizon, and feature list.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/SKILL.md:177:3. If verdict is `fail`: route back to `modeling` with the `remediation_hypothesis`. After modeling fixes the script and reruns, delegate `forecast-reviewer` again. Repeat until verdict is `pass`.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/SKILL.md:180:`forecast-reviewer` (now implemented) is not a CLI stage — do not checkpoint or scaffold it.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/SKILL.md:282:- [ ] `leakage-guard (post)` passed after modeling self-check and before `forecast-reviewer`/`evaluator`; `leakage_guard_post.json` written with verdict `pass`.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/SKILL.md:283:- [ ] For forecasting tasks: `forecast-reviewer` delegated after `modeling` and before `evaluator`; `forecast_review.json` read; if `fail`, route back to modeling with `remediation_hypothesis` and rerun until `pass`.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/SKILL.md:285:- [ ] For anomaly-detection tasks: `forecast-reviewer` skipped; `evaluation.json` reports anomaly ranking/sanity checks from `../shared/anomaly-detection-contract.md`, and progression currently uses `beats_last_promoted` only because anomaly-specific last-promoted fields are not yet defined in `EvaluationSchema`.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/experiment/SKILL.md:287:- [ ] `forecast-reviewer` warnings (if any) recorded in `runs/{run_id}.md` before closeout.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/evaluator/SKILL.md:151:  \"recommended_next\": \"experiment-review\"\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/evaluator/SKILL.md:155:`evaluation.json` fields and enum values must match `gl_tabular.cli.utils.experiment.artifact_schemas.EvaluationSchema`. Required fields and valid values are enforced by CLI validators. `recommended_next` routing is canonical in `gl_tabular.cli.utils.experiment.routing.route_after_evaluator`.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/evaluator/SKILL.md:251:- **Non-forecasting tasks**: recommended next stage is `experiment-review` with decision `discard`, or the earliest upstream stage that must be rerun if the failure is fixable inside the same iteration.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/evaluator/SKILL.md:252:- **Anomaly-detection tasks**: recommended next stage is `experiment-review` with decision `discard`, or `modeling` if the failure is a fixable score direction, threshold, contamination, or prediction-artifact issue. Do not route to `forecast-reviewer`.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/evaluator/SKILL.md:253:- **Forecasting tasks — code bug failures** (`inference_mode_mismatch`, `recursive_parity_stub_detected`, wrong artifact filename, missing required fields): fix the evaluation or modeling script inline, re-run the evaluation, and re-checkpoint `evaluator`. Do **not** route to `forecast-reviewer` for code bugs — `forecast-reviewer` diagnoses forecast quality, not script defects. Record the fix as a technical correction in `current.md`, not as a new hypothesis iteration.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/evaluator/SKILL.md:254:- **Forecasting tasks — model quality failures** (parity delta > `PARITY_DELTA_THRESHOLD`, flat-line/variation collapse, prediction scale anomaly): recommended next stage is `forecast-reviewer` — the orchestrator needs a concrete root-cause and remediation hypothesis before discarding.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/modeling/SKILL.md:215:After generating predictions, immediately run these checks before writing metrics or handing off to `evaluator`. Do not wait for evaluator or forecast-reviewer to discover these issues — catch and fix them inline.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/modeling/SKILL.md:290:- Do not hand off to `forecast-reviewer` or `evaluator`. Re-examine feature engineering or model choice before retraining.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/modeling/SKILL.md:321:- Do not hand off to `forecast-reviewer` or `evaluator`. Re-examine feature engineering or model choice before retraining.\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/modeling/SKILL.md:346:5. Staircase check (run by forecast-reviewer) must pass before evaluator is delegated\ngl_tabular/templates/skills/modeling/SKILL.md:356:A model with a better primary metric but flat, staircase, or collapsed predictions is always worse than a model with a worse metric but realistic variation. `forecast-reviewer` will reject unrealistic predictions before `evaluator` runs — optimizing the primary metric at the expense of realism wastes an iteration.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
